<?xml version="1.0" encoding="ISO-8859-1" standalone="no"?> 
<!DOCTYPE MAN SYSTEM "../../man.dtd">
<MAN>
  <LANGUAGE>eng</LANGUAGE>
  <TITLE>mean  </TITLE>
  <TYPE>Scilab Function  </TYPE>
  <DATE>Januray 1998  </DATE>
  <SHORT_DESCRIPTION name="mean"> mean (row mean, column mean) of vector/matrix entries  </SHORT_DESCRIPTION>
  <CALLING_SEQUENCE>
  <CALLING_SEQUENCE_ITEM>y=mean(x)  </CALLING_SEQUENCE_ITEM>
  <CALLING_SEQUENCE_ITEM>y=mean(x,&apos;r&apos;)  </CALLING_SEQUENCE_ITEM>
  <CALLING_SEQUENCE_ITEM>y=mean(x,&apos;c&apos;)  </CALLING_SEQUENCE_ITEM>
  </CALLING_SEQUENCE>
  <PARAM>
 <PARAM_INDENT>
  <PARAM_ITEM>
  <PARAM_NAME>x  </PARAM_NAME>
  <PARAM_DESCRIPTION>
    : real vector or matrix 
  </PARAM_DESCRIPTION> 
  </PARAM_ITEM>
  <PARAM_ITEM>
  <PARAM_NAME>y  </PARAM_NAME>
  <PARAM_DESCRIPTION>
    : scalar or vector
  </PARAM_DESCRIPTION> 
  </PARAM_ITEM>
 </PARAM_INDENT>
  </PARAM>
  <DESCRIPTION>
  <P>
    For a vector or a matrix <VERB>x</VERB>, <VERB>y=mean(x)</VERB>  returns in the
    scalar <VERB>y</VERB> the mean of all the entries of <VERB>x</VERB>.
  </P>
  <P>
    <VERB>y=mean(x,&apos;r&apos;)</VERB> (or, equivalently, <VERB>y=mean(x,1)</VERB>) is the
    rowwise mean. It returns a row vector:
     <VERB>y(j)= mean(x(:,j))</VERB>
  </P>
  <P>
  </P>
  <P>
  </P>
  <P>
    <VERB>y=mean(x,&apos;c&apos;)</VERB> (or, equivalently, <VERB>y=mean(x,2)</VERB>) is the
    columnwise mean. It returns a column  vector: <VERB>y(i)= mean(x(i,:))</VERB>
  </P>
  <P>
  </P>
  </DESCRIPTION>
  <EXAMPLE><![CDATA[
A=[1,2,10;7,7.1,7.01];
mean(A)
mean(A,'r')
mean(A,'c')
 ]]></EXAMPLE>
